 -- Jean-Charles Lefebvre <polyvertex@gmail.com>  Wed, 12 Jan 2011 10:21:44 +0100

gpsrecorder (1.2.222) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed: Named snapped points were written with a wrong chunk ID in GPSR file and did not appear in KML/GPX exports.
  * Fixed: CSV separator was read incorrectly from configuration file.
  * Modified: Some cosmetics on main window.
  * Added: A track can be appended to an existing GPSR file.
  * Added: Means of transportation can optionally be written in GPSR file.
  * Added: 'HorizEP' field on main window to show the current horizontal position uncertainty value.
  * Added: 'Battery' field on main window (charge level is notified by DBus system, no polling is performed).
  * Added: GPSR files can be converted to TXT files for debug purpose.
  * Removed: Removed 'Snap' menu since there is a 'Snap' button on the main window.

 -- Jean-Charles Lefebvre <polyvertex@gmail.com>  Wed, 03 Nov 2010 19:07:50 +0100

